Global onshore household investable wealth and potential revenue margins by wealth band ($TN), 2024-2029E

1. Onshore only. Notes: Investable wealth is defined as investable personal financial assets including investable assets (deposits, equities, bonds, mutual funds and alternatives), excluding assets held in insurance policies, pensions and direct real estate or any other real assets. Numbers for all years were converted to $ at the year-end 2024 exchange rates to exclude the effect of currency fluctuations. Excludes low mass affluent segment (<300K). Source: Oliver Wyman Wealth Pools 2025.
